        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add scoped mention pattern policy",
        "body": "## Summary\n- add a shared scoped mention-pattern policy for global, agent, and provider/channel overrides\n- apply configured mention-pattern gating across channel runtimes while preserving native mentions\n- document raw regex-body syntax and regenerate config/help metadata\n\n## Notes\n- Recreated from a clean `origin/main` branch after #70846 was closed as dirty; this branch has been rebased on current `origin/main` and generated baselines refreshed after upstream movement.\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 install --lockfile-only --ignore-scripts=false --config.engine-strict=false --config.enable-pre-post-scripts=true --config.side-effects-cache=true`\n- `pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check`\n- `pnpm config:channels:check`\n- `pnpm test extensions/qa-channel/src/inbound.test.ts src/channels/mention-pattern-policy.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-context.body.test.ts`\n- `pnpm check:changed`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** Scoped mention-pattern policy now resolves the effective provider/agent/conversation policy so configured regex mentions are enabled only for explicitly allowed conversations in deny mode and remain disabled for denied or unlisted conversations. Latest follow-up rebased onto current `origin/main`, resolved refreshed Plugin SDK baseline conflicts, and reran the exact-head behavior proof.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw PR checkout on host `patrick`, branch `feature/mention-pattern-policy-clean`, head `3d716ed7164bd1919be1bf5191e4c1088a777ce3`, running the real source resolver, Telegram group peer id helper, mention matcher, and inbound mention decision code through Node/tsx against redacted OpenClaw-style config/message facts. This does not exercise live external delivery.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:** `cd /home/patrick/projects/openclaw-mention-pattern-policy && HEAD_SHA=3d716ed7164bd1919be1bf5191e4c1088a777ce3 HEAD_SHORT=3d716ed716 node --import tsx /tmp/pr70864-proof-c770334.mjs`\n- **Evidence after fix:** Terminal output from the real source smoke:\n\n```text\nOpenClaw scoped mention policy Telegram media pre-download proof (3d716ed716, 3d716ed7164bd1919be1bf5191e4c1088a777ce3)\n{\"topic\":7,\"conversationId\":\"-1001234567893:topic:7\",\"mentionPatternsEnabled\":true,\"wasMentioned\":true,\"shouldSkip\":false,\"skipReason\":null}\n{\"topic\":9,\"conversationId\":\"-1001234567893:topic:9\",\"mentionPatternsEnabled\":false,\"wasMentioned\":false,\"shouldSkip\":true,\"skipReason\":null}\n{\"topic\":11,\"conversationId\":\"-1001234567893:topic:11\",\"mentionPatternsEnabled\":false,\"wasMentioned\":false,\"shouldSkip\":true,\"skipReason\":null}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** In inherited `deny` mode, the media pre-download path honors the Telegram account policy rather than the global provider fallback: account-allowed topic `-1001234567893:topic:7` enables configured regex mention `bot` and media pre-download is not skipped, while account-denied topic `:topic:9` and unlisted topic `:topic:11` disable configured regex mentions and skip unaddressed group media before download.\n- **What was not tested:** Full live external Telegram delivery was not exercised in this proof; CI and targeted channel tests cover the integration paths.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
